cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.IR

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for plant shape analysis, specifically focusing on stem segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep learning approach, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of control-point-based ground truth method suggests a possible connection to robotics, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper deals with plant phenotyping, which could potentially fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
